    "narrative": "The analytics favor **Corbin Carroll** as our definitive anchor today; his score of 85.94 is bolstered by a favorable matchup against Taijuan Walker and an elite spot in the two-hole. While the 1.86s pop time of the opposing catcher creates a marginal drag, his capacity for multi-category production\u2014specifically in our scarcest category, stolen bases\u2014makes him the clear offensive engine. Joining him in the \"Strong\" tier are **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.92), both of whom capitalize on high-upside matchups against Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1rquez and Erick Fedde, respectively. **Mickey Moniak** specifically benefits from the slow delivery of M\u00e1rquez, creating a prime environment for base-path aggression, while **Vinnie Pasquantino** anchors the UTIL spot by taking advantage of a favorable platoon split.\n\nThe decision-making process for the fringes of our lineup was rigorous, with **Seiya Suzuki** standing as the most significant exclusion. Despite a solid score of 50.78, **Seiya Suzuki** failed to crack the starting nine because his opponent, Braxton Ashcraft, limits his ceiling through strong secondary pitches, and the lack of a confirmed lineup heightens our risk aversion. We are opting for the stability of **Alex Freeland** (52.28) and **Max Muncy** (52.79) despite their lower base projections because their specific platoon environments and projected spots in the order offer slightly better efficiency than the bench alternatives like **Trevor Story** or **Zach McKinstry**.\n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" designations across the board. While we have projected **Dalton Rushing**, **Gabriel Moreno**, **Josh Naylor**, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **Alex Freeland**, **Max Muncy**, **Jose Caballero**, **Giancarlo Stanton**, **Mickey Moniak**, **James Wood**, **Tyler Soderstrom**, **Corbin Carroll**, and **Vinnie Pasquantino** based on standard role expectations, any late-breaking changes\u2014particularly those dropping players down the batting order\u2014would disproportionately impact our efficiency scores. Note the wind-aided boost for **Dalton Rushing** and **Alex Freeland**, which helps mitigate the negative impact of their projected #8 hole; monitor these conditions closely before first pitch to ensure these projected outcomes remain viable.",
